The construction of Position Roi Overlay
PositionRoi Overlay is a overlay and also is a control handler, so the 2 main functions are Draw() and OnMouseEvent()
Red: invoked by draw() or OnMouseEvent() directly
Blue: invoked by red directly
Purple: invoked by blue directly
Green: pure private methods to calculate some useful parameters
Also, setting model proxy and getting special info is necessary

The principle of 3D drawing
Rotate: a Vector * a matrix = another Vector
Move: a Vector * a matrix = another Vector
Rmatrix =
| x0, x1, x2 |
| y0, y1, y2 |
| z0, z1, z2 |
Rmatrix
| 1, 0, 0, mx |
| 0, 1, 0, my |
| 0, 0, 1, mz |
Mmatrix =
Mmatrix =
Rotate and Move a Vector * a matrix = another Vector
| mx |
|(Rmatrix) my |
| mz |
R&Mmatrix =
R&Mmatrix
Step1: get a normal vector.
Step2: get a matrix
Step3: multiply them
DrawParallel()
Get two points of a line on the slab
Transform these two pints to other two points using the same matrix
Draw a new line on these two points
Draw all lines parallel to the line
Get pen (colour, style, width)
Only draw line in rectangle
NOTICE:
1be careful when it is n * or (n + )* because atan(), tan and cot does not have value
Draw lines up to down, left to right
2only draw half of all lines, from bottom left to top right0<angle< /2and from top left to
bottom right /2 <angle<
3draw all lines
/2 <angle< 0<angle< /2
From the start point in slab center position, draw until there is not any point in the
frame

Sample CodeGetTransformMatrix ()
/**
* This function is to get transform matrix from self space to view space with rotate
* angle, translate and zoom value
* @param rotate_angle The rotation angle of base position overlay.
* @param translate Translate value of base position overlay.
* @param zoom Zoom value of base position overlay
* @since 1.00
*/
HRESULT MamPositionRoiOverlay::GetTransformMatrix(
VxrVector3 rotate_angle, //the rotate angle matrix
VxrVector3 translate, // offset of the original point of the coordinates
VxrVector3 zoom, //the zoom value of the whole image
VxrMatrix34& matrix //the transform_matrix to get
){
// Get the rotation matrix
VxrMatrix34 rotation_matrix;
VxrEulerMatrixUtilities::GetMatrixFromEulerAngles( rotation_matrix, rotate_angle )
//VxrVector3 translate_vec = rotation_matrix.Transform(translate);
// Get the translation matrix after rotation
VxrMatrix34 translate_matrix = VxrMatrix34::Translate(translate);
// Get the zoom matrix (the final matrix after all the operation
VxrMatrix34 zoom_matrix = VxrMatrix34::Scale(zoom);
matrix = zoom_matrix.Mult(translate_matrix).Mult(rotation_matrix);
return S_OK;
}
Sample Code DrawCube()
for ( int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {// 4 vertical edges
int j = i * 3;
int a = j;
int b = j + 1;
int c = j + RECTANGLE_VERTEX_XYZ;
int d = j + RECTANGLE_VERTEX_XYZ + 1;
idc->DrawLine(points[a], points[b], points[c], points[d], &pen);
lines.slab_id = m_slab_id.copy();
lines.slice_id = slice_serial_number;
//is_intersection: 0 slab, 1 intersection_plane
//line_type: 1 Group, 2 Outline, 3 Center, 4 center cube
lines.is_intersection = 0;
if (drawing_type == 3) {
lines.line_type = 4;
} else {
lines.line_type = slab_display_mode;
}
lines.point1_x = points[a]; lines.point1_y = points[b];
lines.point2_x = points[c]; lines.point2_y = points[d];
m_line_list.push_back(lines);
//intersect
CheckInIntersectionPlane(points[j], points[j + 1], points[j + 2],
points[j + 12], points[j + 13], points[j + 14],
&is_in_intersection, &point_x, &point_y);
if (is_in_intersection == TRUE) {
StPointXYStruct point_xy;
point_xy.point_x = point_x;
point_xy.point_y = point_y;
slab_intersection_list.push_back(point_xy);
}
}
Sample Code DrawRadial()
//transform to the length in view model
length_x_screen = (float)CovertMMToPixels(length_x);
length_y_screen = (float)CovertMMToPixels(length_y);
length_z_screen = (float)CovertMMToPixels(length_z);
//slabs position = original + offset
original_x = original_x + position_x; // also deal with y and z
for (int current_slice = 1; current_slice < slice_num + 1; current_slice++)
{
m_position_app_container_model->
GetSliceVisibility(m_slab_id, current_slice,&slice_visibility);
if (!slice_visibility) continue;
//draw petals
TransPatientAngleToViewAngle(patient_angle_x, patient_angle_y, patient_angle_z + (current_slice - 1) *
HALF_CIRCLE_ANGLE / slice_num, &angle_x, &angle_y, &angle_z, p_transform_manager);
TransformPatientToScreen3D(original_x, original_y, original_z, &screen_original_x, &screen_original_y,
&screen_original_z, p_transform_manager);//get the center of slab
rotate_angle.SetElem(0, angle_x); //y, z
translate.SetElem(0, screen_original_x); //y, z
GetTransformMatrix(rotate_angle, translate, zoom, matrix);
//draw others..
}
Sample Code GetAllPen()
HRESULT MamPositionRoiOverlay::GetAllPen(
CComBSTR slab_id
) {
short red = 0, green = 0, blue = 0;
short current_slab_line_type = 1; // Now, except slab, slice center cube, the indicators are all solid line
IcfPen pen; //using IcfPen
m_position_app_container_model->GetSlabColor(slab_id, SlabRgb, &red, &green, &blue);
short slab_line_type = 0;
m_position_app_container_model->GetLineType(slab_id, SlabType, &slab_line_type);
pen = IcfDrawContextHelpers::CreatePen(
(float)red / PEN_FULL_COLOR,
(float)green / PEN_FULL_COLOR,
(float)blue / PEN_FULL_COLOR);
pen.thickness = PEN_THICKNESS;
pen.nib = e_ipn_square;
if (slab_line_type == 1) {
pen.dash_length = PEN_DASH_LENGTH_SOLID;
pen.space_length = PEN_SPACE_LENGTH_SOLID;
} else {
pen.dash_length = PEN_DASH_LENGTH_DASH;
pen.space_length = PEN_SPACE_LENGTH_DASH;
}
m_slab_unselect_pen = pen;
}
